fields.content: You arrive at the house of the Chief of Police. {steve_home?It looks like her husband is home.:}
fields.title: Chief's House

fields.content: You see Steve Carmell enter the house.
fields.title: Steve Arrives

fields.content: You see Steve Carmell leave the house.
fields.title: Steve Departs

fields.content: {steve_home?{night?The lights turn on suddenly. :}Steve is standing in the bedroom, looking both perplexed and increasingly angry. :The Chief's bedroom looks more practical than functional, but perhaps you'll be able to find something here.}
fields.title: Chief Bedroom

fields.content: The Chief's husband looks out from behind the door. "Can I help you?"
fields.title: Steve at the Threshold

fields.content: You find some documents that look quite thoroughly suspicious. The documents have many romantic flourishes and all share the signed initials RL. From the letters, you gather that this RL was previously in the Black Hand and has been trying to leave for years. You doubt that the initials would be enough to locate her, though.
fields.title: Incriminating Documents

fields.content: The bookcase looks to be a complete mess. It's probably going to take you a while to try to search it.
fields.title: Bookcase

fields.content: Steve sits in his armchair, waiting for your questions.
fields.title: Heart to Heart

fields.content: With a choked sob, Steve confesses to his affair, telling you the name of his mistress: Renee Lilac. He swears he'll break it off if you don't tell the Chief.
fields.title: Confessions

fields.content: You find a picture deep in the drawers of a woman of Italian descent. You take it with you. You could probably identify her if you saw her, but you have no idea where to start looking.
fields.title: Picture

fields.content: That's one sturdy door.
You climb the fire escape and head into the second story window.
You can't quite reach the fire escape.
You knock on the door, and hear an unlatching sound as Steve Carmell answers the door.
You leave the premises.
No one answers.
You break down the door.
"Look, I'm a busy fella. I just have a few questions. Let me in, and we can resolve this quickly."
Would have thought that the Chief of Police's husband would have had better self defense training. Oh well. You drag him into a corner of the sitting room.
"Don't suppose you could let me in to talk, sweetie? It's a bit chilly out here." With a sly grin, he steps aside.
"Umm... You know, I can get pretty scary when I get angry, so maybe you could just let me in, please...?" He doesn't look convinced.
"What's that behind you!" He eyes you suspiciously.

"Don't suppose you could let me in to talk, sweetie? It's a bit chilly out here."

"I'm not interested."

fields.conditions: steve_home and break_in and not steve_unconscious
fields.content: Looks like Steve is not taking kindly to your break in. That's awfully inconsiderate.

fields.conditions: steve_home and break_in and not steve_unconscious

fields.content: After a methodical search, you find some papers of interest.
The bookcase catches your attention.
You stumble across a bookcase in the dark.

fields.conditions: steve_home and not steve_unconscious and not break_in
fields.content: "You wanted to talk? Let's talk."
Well, it looks like your time is up. Steve walks in the door and sees you.
You find nothing of interest.
Your search reveals nothing.

"Why did you do it?"
According to his account, she's a member of some gang and has been trying desperately to leave. In his haste to help her, the two developed a bond.

"I can't promise anything."
You make no promises and leave the man to his grief.

"Where can I find her?"
He isn't sure, but she first approached him near the docks.

fields.helper: I don't want either of you to get hurt.
fields.content:
"I don't want either of you to get hurt."
He looks immensely relieved.
"I really don't have time to sit around and exchange pleasantries. Tell me about the affair."
You begin a tirade, but in the middle of it, your voice cracks. He doesn't look very intimidated.
Before he can get another word in, you hit him over the head with a candelabra. He slumps to the ground.
"The Chief knows what's been going on. She sent me to resolve this quietly. Let's just get this out into the open so that we can figure out how to resolve this."
"Well... you know that most married couples are happier when they're honest with each other, right? ...I suppose not that I would know from personal experience..."

fields.conditions: not steve_unconscious and steve_home and not night
fields.content: "I thought you wanted to talk, not peruse our collection of books." He eyes you suspiciously and gestures to one of the seats.
